AUDIO: 'let\'s just get it to generate one image. And then if you\'ve been following my channel, you should be familiar with this case sampler component. The seed is basically the starting point of your image because there could be basically'

[28:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'almost an infinite amount of generations it could make with this prompt. And this seed is just one of them. Now, usually you would just set this to random, but if you set the same seed number and you keep the rest of the settings the same,'

[28:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it will generate the exact same image as before. And then steps is how many well steps you want the AI to go through before outputting your final image. So, in general, the more steps you have, the longer it will take to generate, but'

[29:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re going to get better quality. But at a certain point, if your step count is too high, like over 50 steps, you\'re going to get diminishing returns. And then conversely, if you set the step count to a lower value, like 10 steps, it\'s going to generate faster, but at'

[29:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the sacrifice of some quality. And then CFG is how literally you want the AI to follow your prompt over here. A high CFG value would get the AI to follow this really literally and really try to'

[29:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
